## Current Known Context

- Airplane drop modes remain: bonus drop, coin trail, spotlight, lucky wind, police delay (boost lane removed as confusing).
- Plane drop dispatch/fallback remains in `src/game/planeDropRuntime.ts` and is retry-safe.
- Plane drop coordinates center directly under the airplane (no y-offset).
- Plane flyover sound plays when the plane enters the viewport (`flyoverSoundPlayed` flag), not at encounter creation.
- All encounter/effect/spawn orchestration is extracted to focused runtime helpers.
- `Game.ts` retains only side-effect orchestration, core loop, and render assembly.
- Police car wheels match player car style (black boxes with white border).
- Police car body and airplane contours have white borders for bright-page visibility.
- Airplane sprite: narrower wings (wingSpan 28), wider body (bodyWidth 12, bodyLength 28), wider tail (tailWidth 8, tailHeight 8).
- Scanner classifies `img`, `picture`, `video`, `canvas` as `ice`; `svg` remains `boost`.
- Scanner detects YouTube/Vimeo iframes via `src` URL match and classifies them as `ice`.
- `window.__domRacerDebug` must not exist in source/build.
- Overgrowth data model and spawn logic live in `src/game/overgrowthRuntime.ts`.
- Overgrowth rendering lives in `gameRenderRuntime.ts` (`drawOvergrowthNodes`), called from `Game.ts` render pipeline.
- Overgrowth spawns from barrier/obstacle edges after 35s run threshold, 9-15s spawn interval, max 8 nodes.
- Overgrowth stages: small (10px depth, slow zone) -> medium (20px, slow zone, after 6s) -> large (32px, obstacle/wall, after 10s more).
- Overgrowth kinds: bush (55% chance, leafy blob clusters) and tree (45% chance, round canopy with trunk center).
- Overgrowth rendering: green palette darkening by stage, smooth entry scale/alpha animation, gentle sin-wave sway, large-stage outline for readability.
- Overgrowth collision: small/medium stages merged into player slow zones, large stages merged into player obstacles and pickup spawn blockers.
- Overgrowth state resets on beginRun and stop.
- Overgrowth sprites shown in `Shift+D` showcase (3 bush stages + 3 tree stages).
- Near-miss detection logic lives in `src/game/nearMissRuntime.ts`.
- Near-miss uses expand-and-check: expand player rect by 5px, check intersection without collision against obstacles and police.
- Near-miss awards +3 to +5 score per trigger, 800ms cooldown between triggers.
- Near-miss skipped when player is airborne or ghost mode active.
- Near-miss toast: rotating CLOSE!/TIGHT!/RAZOR!/WHEW! in orange (#fb923c), 600ms TTL, low priority.
- Near-miss flavor text at 4+ ("Living on the edge. Literally.") and 8+ ("Thread the needle much?") count thresholds.
- Near-miss state (cooldownMs, count, flavorIndex) resets on beginRun and stop.
- Near-miss toast words added to sprite showcase debug mode.
- Micro-objective logic lives in `src/game/microObjectiveRuntime.ts`.
- 8 objective templates: collect 5/8/12 coins, 8 coins in 20s, reach 80 pts, 3 close calls, grab special, survive 20s, FLOW x5.
- One active objective at a time, assigned after 6-10s initial delay, then 4-8s between completions, 3-5s after expiry.
- On completion: +25 score bonus, rotating toast (NAILED!/DONE!/CLEAR!/CHECK!) in violet (#a78bfa).
- On failure/timeout: silently expires, new objective assigned after short delay.
- Survive-duration objectives succeed when timer expires (player stayed alive).
- HUD: bottom-center panel with ★ label, progress text, thin violet progress bar.
- Objective state (active, delay, completed count, last template) resets on beginRun and stop.
- Flavor text at 3+ objectives ("Checking boxes like a pro.") and 6+ ("Objective machine. HR wants a word.").
- No duplicate template assignment in a row; score-threshold skip if score ≥80% of target.
- Jackpot pickup: very rare special (~6% chance per special spawn roll), 26px golden star sprite with pulsing glow and sparkle particles.
- Jackpot awards +50-100 score (random), instant activation, no timer, "JACKPOT!" toast in gold (#facc15).
- Jackpot is NOT in `RANDOM_SPECIAL_EFFECTS`; spawns via separate chance roll before `pickSpecialEffect`.
- Jackpot has longer spawn cue ring (1800ms vs 1200ms) and `value: 0` (score comes from activation).
- 8 special effects total: bonus, magnet, invert, ghost, blackout, cooldown, lure, jackpot.
- README includes indie/playful voice, "why this is fun" section, living roadmap table, airplane events section, overgrowth/near-miss/micro-objectives sections, and screenshots & motion placeholder section.
